data.value:
This is a very simple C# app to add an icon to the Windows Taskbar so you can easily run commands, launch applications, or otherwise make your own quick shortcuts.
No more making shortcuts to batch files to run your common Command Prompt tasks, of course you can still kind of do that here for more complex tasks. I made this tool to stop and start the Synergy mouse service. And to quickly change the display settings without having to dig around in the windows settings.
This is a 'portable' app that needs no install. The menu is easily customisable by editing a CSV file in the same location as the EXE. The CSV file will be created if it does not exist. And that example file should be a good starting point to make your own custom task launcher.
Visit the github project for more info.
